ANOTHER taxi owner was allegedly shot dead in Alexandra. The taxi operator ambushed by armed suspects as he was
driving into his home. Police and pathology services are currently on scene. This follows the recent shocking killing of the Chairperson of the Alexandra Randburg, Midrand and Sandton Taxi Association (ARMSTA) Sam Budza on the 13th of July. At the time Budza was accompanied by cops and bodyguards after a meeting, when he was on his way home, then he was shot dead. One of his bodyguards was allegedly also shot dead and another bodyguard was seriously injured. While on the weekend, a taxi that was travelling from a funeral at Ematimatolo back to Joburg, in Gauteng was ambushed by a group of armed men in KwaZulu-Natal. A total of 11 people were killed and only two survived without any injuries. The incident reportedly occurred along the R74 road between Colenso and Weenen. 